eu.cqse.check.framework.typetracker.java

Class JavaImportSensitiveTypeResolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.typetracker.java.JavaImportSensitiveTypeResolver

  • public class JavaImportSensitiveTypeResolver
extends java.lang.Object
    Allows resolving the type of variables and constructor calls in an import-sensitive manner. Methods can be assumed to return values of some type. Can also be used to check whether some type is imported.

      • isOfType

        public boolean isOfType(java.util.List<IToken> tokens,
                        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> fullyQualifiedTypeNames,
                        ScopedTypeLookup lookup,
                        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> methods,
                        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> staticMethods)
        Checks whether the last expression in tokens is of one of the specified fully qualified types. Assume this is true if the expression is a call to a method in methods, or in staticMethods, which should be as qualified as they're expected to appear in code.
        Limitations:
        • We don't handle nested classes as types
        • We only automatically check constructor calls and the local typing context
        • We don't handle superfluous enclosing parenthesis, e.g. (foo).method
